title: NFL inactives: Andrew Luck back for Colts against Patriots
text:
By The Associated Press October 18, 2015 7:50 pm 
After missing two games in a row with an injured right shoulder, Colts quarterback Andrew Luck was active again. 
Luck was expected to start Sunday night against the visiting New England Patriots. 
New England linebacker Dont’a Hightower, who had been listed as questionable with a rib injury, was inactive. 
He is second on the team with 26 total tackles and is third with 2 1/2 sacks.
